The paper deals with the problem of generating shared random keys using limited communication and i.i.d. samples from a known random source, which is a fundamental problem in cryptography and has connections to communication under uncertainty and locality sensitive hashing. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), and Machine Learning (cs.MM) sub-categories.
